# DOM Mutation Safety
- Any markdown HTML must go through `renderDocument()` sanitization before DOM insertion.
- Restrict `innerHTML` usage to approved rendering boundaries (`renderIntoElement`, TOC container reset, controlled mount reset).
- For dynamic text/UI labels, prefer `textContent` and DOM node APIs over HTML string concatenation.
- Keep host-page impact minimal: mount extension UI only inside the dedicated viewer root (`mdp-viewer-root` + Shadow DOM when available).
- When adding event listeners to generated nodes, provide teardown paths (`destroy()`/removeEventListener) to avoid leaks.
